BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:From: Windbigler\, Faith (zyx5rs) <zyx5rs@virginia.edu<mailto:z
 yx5rs@virginia.edu>>\nDate: Wednesday\, March 11\, 2026 at 2:48 PM\nTo: 
 Solomon\, Ian H. (ihs8m) <ihs8m@virginia.edu<mailto:ihs8m@virginia.edu>>\n
 Cc: Thurston\, Kerra K (kkt8c) <kkt8c@virginia.edu<mailto:kkt8c@virginia.e
 du>>\nSubject: Coffee & Karaoke!\nDear Dean Solomon\,\n\nHappy spring!\n\n
 Following up on what you said in class\, I would love to get coffee again 
 whenever you have time. I have refined much of my thinking about my goals 
 for the rest of my time here—and\, hopefully\, through future involvemen
 t with the Batten Alumni Advisory Board—as well as my research on studen
 ts’ concerns. I would love to get your input and talk about what might b
 e actionable before the start of next year. My schedule is quite flexible 
 for the next few weeks\, especially during mornings\, so I can do whatever
  time works best for you.\n\nNow that the weather is warm\, we would also 
 love to do Karaoke again! Given that we have Policy Ball on March 28 and F
 ourth Year Dinner on April 7\, anything the week of March 30 or April 13 w
 ould be wonderful.\n\nThank you so much for coming to speak to us today\, 
 too. I always value your insights on leadership.\n\nWarm regards\,\nFaith 
 Windbigler\n--\nFaith Windbigler\nUniversity of Virginia\nB.A. Public Poli
 cy & Leadership | Class of 2026\nBatten Undergraduate Council President\n(
 720) 364-2837\nzyx5rs@virginia.edu<mailto:zyx5rs@virginia.edu>\n\n\n\n
