BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:From: Barrera Paredes\, Suliana Rachel (hnf3pt) <hnf3pt@virgini
 a.edu<mailto:hnf3pt@virginia.edu>>\nSent: Thursday\, March 12\, 2026 8:00 
 AM\nTo: Thurston\, Kerra K (kkt8c) <kkt8c@virginia.edu<mailto:kkt8c@virgin
 ia.edu>>\nCc: Cook\, Ellen C (ecc5qn) <ecc5qn@virginia.edu<mailto:ecc5qn@v
 irginia.edu>>\nSubject: BLN Welcome Event for Admitted Students\n\nGood mo
 rning Kerra\,\n\nI hope you are doing well! My name is Suliana\, I'm a fou
 rth-year Batten student on the Lawn! I'm reaching out to propose an event 
 that would be hosted by the Batten Latinx Network. Since Batten's applicat
 ion decisions are out\, we want to host Batten admittees and current stude
 nts for a Welcome party. If possible\, could Dean Solomon open his Pavilio
 n garden for this event on April 3rd from 5-6:30 pm? This would be a great
  opportunity for new students to connect with Dean Solomon (with Dante)\, 
 Batten faculty and staff\, current Batten students\, and the rest of the n
 ew cohort. I have attached Ellen Cook\, our new Assistant Director of Stud
 ent Engagement\, so she can remain in the loop. Thank you for your time\, 
 and I hope you can consider our request!\n\nBest wishes\,\n\nSuliana Barre
 ra Paredes (she/her/ella)\nUniversity of Virginia | B.A. Public Policy & L
 eadership and Spanish| 2026\nE: hnf3pt@virginia.edu<mailto:hnf3pt@virginia
 .edu>\n\n
