BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:From: Hill\, Archie Holden (xej7ej) <xej7ej@virginia.edu<mailto
 :xej7ej@virginia.edu>>\nSent: Wednesday\, April 15\, 2026 11:35 PM\nTo: Th
 urston\, Kerra K (kkt8c) <kkt8c@virginia.edu<mailto:kkt8c@virginia.edu>>\n
 Cc: Solomon\, Ian H. (ihs8m) <ihs8m@virginia.edu<mailto:ihs8m@virginia.edu
 >>\nSubject: Reserving Pavilion X Space for Event Inquiry\n\nGood evening 
 Ms. Thurston\,\n\nMy name is Holden Hill and I am a current 3rd year Batte
 n student at UVA. I am one of the current chairs for the Virginia Guide Se
 rvice\, a CIO on Grounds that gives historical tours of the university. I 
 was hoping to reserve garden space for an event we are having for our newl
 y initiated tour guides on April 26th\, but have been having trouble locat
 ing the direct site to book space. 25Live does not seem to be working. I w
 as wondering if it would be possible to reserve the Pavilion X garden spac
 e for this initiation event.\n\nIt is my understanding that the front port
 ion of the garden with the patio is private property\, and not open to be 
 booked. May it be possible to use this space with the approval of Dean Sol
 omon? I would be open to assuming all responsibility for the event in the 
 space. If not\, would you be able to help me in trying to reserve the othe
 r garden space in Pavilion X? Thank you so much for your help!\n\nBest reg
 ards\,\n\nArchie Holden Hill V\nUniversity of Virginia\, Class of 2027\nB.
 A. Public Policy and Leadership\nMinor in Data Science\n\n
