DESCRIPTION:From: Hicks\, Hunter Allen (hpz8rm) <hpz8rm@virginia.edu<mailto
 :hpz8rm@virginia.edu>>\nSent: Friday\, April 10\, 2026 4:44:18 PM\nTo: Sol
 omon\, Ian H. (ihs8m) <ihs8m@virginia.edu<mailto:ihs8m@virginia.edu>>\nCc:
  Thurston\, Kerra K (kkt8c) <kkt8c@virginia.edu<mailto:kkt8c@virginia.edu>
 >\nSubject: Re: H2O Water Tasting\n\nHello Dean Solomon\,\n\nAlong with th
 e many other skills learned in Lead from Anywhere\, we learned the art of 
 the follow up email. And\, of course\, learned the best time to send it is
  4:45 on a Friday when no one is checking their email.\n\nI would like to 
 reiterate the success a water tasting could have. I BCC’d a number of my
  Batten Buddies who echo’d excitement of trying water with their dean. I
  also have attached a photo of some of the waters I’ve ordered (some hav
 e been aged 20+ years!). I’m sure professor Myung would agree that there
  is a clear correlation between glass bottles and quality of the water.\n\
 nHope we can make this happen!\n\nHunter Hicks\n\nGet Outlook for iOS<http
 s://aka.ms/o0ukef>\n\nFrom: Hicks\, Hunter Allen (hpz8rm) <hpz8rm@virginia
 .edu<mailto:hpz8rm@virginia.edu>>\nSent: Wednesday\, April 8\, 2026 11:17:
 19 AM\nTo: Solomon\, Ian H. (ihs8m) <ihs8m@virginia.edu<mailto:ihs8m@virgi
 nia.edu>>\nCc: Thurston\, Kerra K (kkt8c) <kkt8c@virginia.edu<mailto:kkt8c
 @virginia.edu>>\nSubject: H2O Water Tasting\n\n
